TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ni, Sophie X
AU  - Pearson, Neil D
AU  - Poteshman, Allen M
AU  - White, Joshua
T1  - Does Option Trading Have a Pervasive Impact on Underlying Stock Prices?
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa082
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 4
SP  - 1952
EP  - 1986
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - The question of whether and to what extent option trading affects underlying stock prices has been of interest to researchers since exchange-based options trading began in 1973. Recent research presents evidence of an informational channel through which option trading affects stock prices by showing that option market makers’ stock trades to hedge new options positions cause the information reflected in option trading to be impounded into underlying equity prices. This paper provides evidence of a noninformational channel through which option market maker hedge rebalancing affects stock return volatility and the probability of large stock price moves.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa082
ER  - 



